Class ClusterLimitedIntRAC

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.ml.clustering.rac.IntRAC
      • org.openimaj.ml.clustering.rac.ClusterLimitedIntRAC
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Clusterer<int[][]>, Readable, ReadableASCII, ReadableBinary, ReadWriteable, Writeable, WriteableASCII, WriteableBinary, Assigner<int[]>, HardAssigner<int[],float[],IntFloatPair>, CentroidsProvider<int[]>, Clusters, SpatialClusterer<IntRAC,int[]>, SpatialClusters<int[]>

    public class ClusterLimitedIntRAC
extends IntRAC
    Similar to IntRAC but explicitly specify the limit the number of clusters. Attempts to replace clusters which are "closer" with those that are "further".

    As with the IntRAC this is a combined clusterer, clusters and assigner. See the IntRAC documentation for more details.

    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk), Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
